name: What's my purpose
description:
Verse 1
Still lost trying to find out what my purpose is,
God and music are the main things in what I'm focused in,
Never paid any attention to the fakes and Illusionist's,
I aint down with hocus pocus sh*t,
Sent here to give y'all the facts,
While these other dudes putting up act's,
I don't pay them no mind no time,
I gotta, I gotta shine so grind for that,
I keep balance so I stay on my 50-50,
I give dap so the people stay f*cking with me,
but I gotta stay in sight stay in mind,
I gotta, I gotta give them my life so they believe me,
So when they see me, they believe me,
So when they see me they believe me,
This another beat by incise,
I'm just trying to give you insight.

There's so much on my mind like how I want to rewind time to see my pre life
better yet fast forward to death, so I can see what's next. Is there afterlife existence? Or is that too distant for me to ponder about? I know I should be more worried about the present, but it haunt's me to know if there is a heaven or a hell, or will I reach freedom or be stuck in jail, Or nothing at all, Is life just a twisted fairy tail? And is my life pre-determined or am I in charge of my own fate? I'm convinced that seeking, believing, and questioning are all tied together. Because if you seek and question you must believe that there is something... but in the end, they are all just verbs. An action.
